  <header class="header">
    <h1>Innovating for Sustainability</h1>
    <p>Driving Smart Resource Conservation (Energy & Water) in Home Appliances</p>
  </header>

  <main class="content">
    <section class="appliance" id="refrigerators">
      <h2>ü•∂ Refrigerators</h2>
      <p><strong>Problems:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>High Energy Consumption</strong> ‚Äì Older or poorly maintained units consume a lot of electricity.</li>
        <li><strong>Refrigerant Emissions</strong> ‚Äì Many still use refrigerants with high Global Warming Potential (GWP).</li>
        <li><strong>Poor Cooling Efficiency</strong> ‚Äì Due to frequent door opening, improper thermostat settings, or overload.</li>
        <li><strong>Compressor Overuse</strong> ‚Äì Lack of smart control leads to constant cycling and reduced lifespan.</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>App-Based Alerts & Control</strong> ‚Äì Remind users to close doors, clean coils, or adjust settings via app.</li>
        <li><strong>Thermal Insulation Enhancements</strong> ‚Äì Improve insulation materials to retain coolness longer.</li>
        <li><strong>Solar-Integrated Power Options</strong> ‚Äì Run using DC compressors powered by solar panels, ideal for remote or sunny areas.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="appliance" id="air-conditioners">
      <h2>‚ùÑÔ∏è Air Conditioners</h2>
      <p><strong>Problems:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Overcooling & Uneven Cooling</strong> ‚Äì Poor room sensing and lack of zoning waste energy.</li>
        <li><strong>Dirty Filters and Poor Maintenance</strong> ‚Äì Reduces efficiency, airflow, and air quality.</li>
        <li><strong>Not Optimized for Climate Zones</strong> ‚Äì Same settings used for different environments reduce efficiency.</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Auto Cleaning & Maintenance Alerts</strong> ‚Äì Prevent filter clogging and improve airflow with app-based reminders.</li>
        <li><strong>Inverter Technology Compressors</strong> ‚Äì Adjust power consumption based on cooling needs, avoiding full-speed operation.</li>
        <li><strong>Solar-Powered AC Units</strong> ‚Äì Reduce grid dependency, especially in high-sun regions.</li>
        <li><strong>Geofencing & Remote Control</strong> ‚Äì Turn off or adjust AC based on user location via smartphone app.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="appliance" id="washing-machines">
      <h2>üß∫ Washing Machines</h2>
      <p><strong>Problems:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Excessive Water Usage</strong> ‚Äì Many models don‚Äôt adjust water based on load size.</li>
        <li><strong>High Energy Consumption</strong> ‚Äì Especially in hot water cycles or when using inefficient motors.</li>
        <li><strong>Limited Greywater Reuse</strong> ‚Äì Water is discarded even when it can be reused for pre-wash or flushing.</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Greywater Reuse System</strong> ‚Äì Store and reuse rinse water for the next pre-wash or toilet flush.</li>
        <li><strong>Smart Load Sensing</strong> ‚Äì Use sensors to adjust water and energy usage based on load weight and fabric type.</li>
        <li><strong>Eco Wash Modes</strong> ‚Äì Lower temperature, shorter duration, and optimized rinse cycles to save resources.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="appliance" id="desert-air-coolers">
      <h2>üå¨Ô∏è Desert Air Coolers</h2>
      <p><strong>Problems:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Excessive Water Usage</strong> ‚Äì Constant evaporation consumes large amounts of water, especially in arid regions.</li>
        <li><strong>Inefficient Cooling in Humid Conditions</strong> ‚Äì They are less effective when humidity levels are high.</li>
        <li><strong>Manual Operation and Poor Control</strong> ‚Äì Lack of smart features leads to unnecessary operation and resource wastage.</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Water Level Sensors & Auto-Shutoff</strong> ‚Äì Prevents dry running and alerts users when water is low, conserving resources.</li>
        <li><strong>Smart Climate-Based Control</strong> ‚Äì Integrates humidity sensors to adjust fan speed or shut down when cooling is ineffective.</li>
        <li><strong>Solar-Powered Operation</strong> ‚Äì Use photovoltaic panels to run the cooler, reducing electricity dependency.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>
